headline: Brown & Brown (NYSE:BRO) Reports US$1,404 Million Revenue, Declares US$0.15 Dividend
summary: Brown & Brown (NYSE:BRO) recently affirmed its quarterly cash dividend of $0.15 per share and announced robust earnings growth for Q1 2025, with revenue climbing to $1,404 million. This financial performance aligns with market trends, as major indices rose, aided by positive earnings reports despite tariff concerns.
